    "causal_summary": "The Lane C skill-benchmark harness parses a skill's router by literal-scanning **`SKILL.md`** for `INTENT_SIGNALS = {` and `RESOURCE_MAP = {`. `sk-code` deliberately delegates its authoritative router to `references/smart_routing.md` (the \"template customization surface\" design) and uses an `INTENT_MODEL` + prose maps, so the harness finds no inline dictionaries. A run reports `router_unparseable` (P0) → `BLOCKED-BY-STRUCTURE`, plus 94 false `orphan_reference` findings. `sk-code` cannot be benchmarked at all.",
